{"id":8437,"date":"2025-09-22T06:20:25","date_gmt":"2025-09-22T06:20:25","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/realtrips.in\/?post_type=trip&#038;p=8437"},"modified":"2025-12-04T11:28:13","modified_gmt":"2025-12-04T11:28:13","slug":"spiritual-chardham","status":"publish","type":"trip","link":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/trip\/spiritual-chardham\/","title":{"rendered":"SPIRITUAL CHARDHAM"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8516,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","destination":[90],"activities":[],"trip_types":[75],"difficulty":[],"trip_tag":[],"wptravelengine_custom_taxonomy_tripcategory":[77],"class_list":["post-8437","trip","type-trip","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","destination-devbhoomi-uttarakhand","trip_types-customized-domestic-tour","tripcategory-customized-domestic-tour"],"packages_ids":[8438],"trip_extras":[],"cut_off_time":{"enabled":false,"duration":0,"duration_unit":"days"},"booked-seats":[],"code":"WTE-8437","price":42777,"has_sale":false,"sale_price":0,"discount_percent":0,"currency":{"code":"INR","symbol":"&#8377;"},"duration":{"days":11,"nights":10,"duration_unit":"days","duration_type":"days"},"min_pax":1,"max_pax":"","discount_value":0,"discount_label":"&#8377;0 Off","primary_category":27,"available_times":{"type":"default","items":["2021-1-01","2021-2-01","2021-3-01","2021-4-01","2021-5-01","2021-6-01","2021-7-01","2021-8-01","2021-9-01","2021-10-01","2021-11-01","2021-12-01"]},"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Embark on a sacred journey to the divine land of Uttarakhand, known as <em>Devbhoomi \u2013 the Land of the Gods<\/em>. The Char Dham Yatra takes you through the four holiest shrines of Hinduism \u2013 <strong>Yamunotri, Gangotri, Kedarnath, and Badrinath<\/strong>. Nestled amidst the majestic Himalayas, each Dham holds deep spiritual significance: Yamunotri, the source of River Yamuna; Gangotri, the origin of River Ganga; Kedarnath, one of Lord Shiva\u2019s twelve Jyotirlingas; and Badrinath, the sacred abode of Lord Vishnu. Along the way, experience breathtaking mountain views, serene river valleys, and a divine aura that uplifts the soul. This pilgrimage is not just a journey of faith but also an opportunity to connect with nature, spirituality, and inner peace.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":" 3 star premium hotel stay\n All transfers and sightseeing by AC Vehicle\n Breakfast, Dinner, Lunch\n Toll Tax\n Parking\n Driver Allowance\nTravel Goodies\n 24 x 7 On tour Assistance\n All cost from EX Destination","cost_excludes":"Any meals other than those mentioned above in inclusions\n Airfare \/ Train Ticket\n GST 5%\n All monument entry Fees\n Any portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all items of personal nature\n Any services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions\nEntrance fees to Monuments & other sightseeing points\nExpenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, vehicle malfunctions, political disturbances, etc.\nAnything not mentioned in inclusions","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"1. Where does the trip start and end? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Yatra usually starts from Haridwar\/Delhi\/Dehradun and ends at the same location.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"2. What kind of accommodation is provided? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hotels, dharamshalas, or guesthouses with neat and clean rooms. In remote locations, facilities may be basic but comfortable.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"3. How difficult is the Char Dham Yatra? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Yatra involves long road journeys and treks (notably to Yamunotri &amp; Kedarnath). Senior citizens and those with health issues should consult their doctor before booking. Helicopter options are available for Kedarnath to reduce trekking distance.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"4. What is the best time to go on the Char Dham Yatra? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Yatra season runs from May to October (temples close in winter). <br>May\u2013June and September\u2013October are considered the best months due to favorable weather.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"5. What should I pack for this journey?  ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Warm clothing (sweaters, jackets, thermals, gloves, socks) <br>Comfortable walking shoes\/trekking shoes Raincoat\/umbrella (monsoon months) <br>Torch, water bottle, personal medicines Valid ID proof (mandatory at hotels &amp; shrines)<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"}],"is_featured":false,"featured_image":{"width":900,"height":596,"file":"2025\/09\/26.png","filesize":680487,"sizes":{"medium":{"file":"26-300x199.png","width":300,"height":199,"filesize":65515,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/26-300x199.png"},"thumbnail":{"file":"26-150x150.png","width":150,"height":150,"filesize":15100,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/26-150x150.png"},"medium_large":{"file":"26-768x509.png","width":768,"height":509,"filesize":292307,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/26-768x509.png"},"trip-thumb-size":{"file":"26-374x226.png","width":374,"height":226,"filesize":41975,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/26-374x226.png"},"destination-thumb-size":{"file":"26-600x596.png","width":600,"height":596,"filesize":283432,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/26-600x596.png"},"destination-thumb-trip-size":{"file":"26-410x250.png","width":410,"height":250,"filesize":47840,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"ht